  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Proverbs 12:24",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 12:24",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The hand of the diligent shall bear rule — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Industry is the way to preferment. An instance of which we have ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 11:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where we learn that Solomon advanced Jeroboam because he saw he was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "an industrious young man. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Men that take pains in an honest employment, and especially those that labour to be useful to others, will thereby gain such an interest and reputation, as will give them a superiority over all about them. Thus many have risen strangely; and he that has been ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "faithful in a few things ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "has been made ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "ruler over many things. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And those who are diligent while they are young, frequently procure that wealth and power which enable them to rule, and so to rest, when they are old; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "but the slothful shall be under tribute — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or, rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the deceitful, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "רמיה",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "signifies. He terms the slothful ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "deceitful, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because deceit and idleness are generally companions; and such persons seek to gain by fraud, by their shifts and arts of dishonesty, what they either cannot, or will not, get by honest labour.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
