  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The hand of the diligent shall bear rule,.... \"Shall become rich\", so Jarchi interprets it, according to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 10:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; Through diligence men get riches, and through riches they arrive to power and authority over others: from apprentices and journeymen workmen they become masters of their business; diligent men become masters of families, and have servants and workmen under them; become magistrates in cities, and bear rule over their fellow citizens, and are advanced to places of power and authority in the commonwealth; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 22:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but the slothful shall be under tribute; the \"slothful\" or \"deceitful hand\" (l), for so it may be rendered and supplied; for usually such who are slothful, and do not care for business, get their living by deceitful methods, by tricking and sharping; and such become subject to others, to them that are diligent; hence said to be \"under tribute\", or tributary; because those that are tributary are in subjection to those to whom they pay tribute. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(l) \"Manus fraudulentiae\", Michaelis; \"dolosa\", Montanus, Junius & Tremellius, Mercerus, Gejerus; \"fraudulenta\", Tigurine version, Vatablus. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(l) \"Manus fraudulentiae\", Michaelis; \"dolosa\", Montanus, Junius & Tremellius, Mercerus, Gejerus; \"fraudulenta\", Tigurine version, Vatablus. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
